enry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Mathilda","meanings":["Old German: Mighty battle maid"]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Matilda Burnell was born about 1218. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with William Touchet."},"et":{"ABT 1218–":"umbes 1218–Surnud","1208–Male":"1208–Surnud","1231–1312":"1231–1312","1266–1332":"1266–1332","1218–Female":"1218–Surnud","1312":"1312","ABT. 1231":"umbes 1231","1266":"1266","1332":"1332","1231":"1231","ABT 1218":"umbes 1218","1208":"1208","1218":"1218","of Haynton, Lincoln, England":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Wollaton, Nottinghamshire, England":"Wollaton, Nottinghamshire, England"},"fi":{"ABT 1218–":"noin 1218–Kuollut","1208–Male":"1208–Kuollut","1231–1312":"1231–1312","1266–1332":"1266–1332","1218–Female":"1218–Kuollut","1312":"1312","ABT. 1231":"noin 1231","1266":"1266","1332":"1332","1231":"1231","ABT 1218":"noin 1218","1208":"1208","1218":"1218","of Haynton, Lincoln, England":"Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Wollaton, Nottinghamshire, England":"Wollaton, Nottinghamshire, England"},"fr":{"ABT 1218–":"environ 1218–Décédée","1208–Male":"1208–Décédé","1231–1312":"1231–1312","1266–1332":"1266–1332","1218–Female":"1218–Décédée","1312":"1312","ABT. 1231":"environ 1231","1266":"1266","1332":"1332","1231":"1231","ABT 1218":"environ 1218","1208":"1208","1218":"1218","of Haynton, Lincoln, England":"Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Wollaton, Nottinghamshire, England":"Wollaton, Nottinghamshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Matilda Burnell est née environ 1218. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils et 1 fille avec William Touchet."},"de":{"ABT 1218–":"um 1218–Verstorben","1208–Male":"1208–Verstorben","1231–1312":"1231–1312","1266–